Feature: Tarantallegra

    Makes victim's legs dance uncontrollably, so the victim cannot control his
    or her movements (recalling the tarantella dance).

    Pronunciation:
        /təˌræntəˈlɛɡrə/ tə-RAN-tə-LEG-rə
    Seen/mentioned:
        First used by Draco on Harry in the Duelling Club in Chamber of
        Secrets. It can be stopped using Finite, as mentioned in Order of the
        Phoenix. It is notably used against Neville in the Department of
        Mysteries, causing the prophecy to be broken.
